		</text>
		
		<text xstart="0.1" ystart="0.3" xend="0.9" yend="0.8" font="arial"
			fontsize="36" fontcolor="#ff000000" alignment="left">
			<richtext bold="true" afterspace = "1">
				Red shift: 
			</richtext>
			<richtext>
				redshift happens when light or other EM radiation from an object is increased in wavelength, or shifted to the red end of the spectrum.\n
			</richtext>
			<richtext bold="true" afterspace = "1">
				Blue shift: 
			</richtext>
			<richtext>
				A blue shift is any decrease in wavelength, with a corresponding increase in frequency, of EM waves.
			</richtext>
		</text>
		
